---
import ThemeToggle from "../components/ThemeToggle";
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Welcome to Astro.">
  <main class="min-h-screen">
    <div
      class="sticky backdrop-blur-sm bg-white/10 dark:bg-black/10 top-0 flex justify-between p-4"
    >
      <p class="text-3xl text-black dark:text-white">bruk.dev</p>
      <ThemeToggle client:load />
    </div>
    <article class="prose mx-auto dark:prose-invert p-4">
      <article>
        <h2>Unique Approach to UI Components</h2>
        <p>
          Unlike traditional UI libraries such as Material UI or Chakra UI,
          which provide bundled components, Shadcn UI offers a <strong
            >collection of reusable components</strong
          > that developers can directly copy and paste into their applications.
          This approach allows for greater flexibility and customization, as developers
          can choose only the components they need without being tied to a larger
          framework.
        </p>

        <h2>Built on Modern Technologies</h2>
        <p>
          Shadcn UI is built on <strong>Tailwind CSS</strong> and <strong
            >Radix UI</strong
          >, which enhances its capabilities in creating responsive and
          accessible user interfaces. It supports various frameworks including
          Next.js, Gatsby, and Vite, making it versatile for different
          development environments. The integration with Tailwind CSS allows for
          rapid styling and customization while maintaining a clean codebase.
        </p>

        <h2>Rapid Adoption and Community Support</h2>
        <p>
          Since its launch, Shadcn UI has garnered significant attention,
          reflected in its impressive metrics: over <strong
            >37,000 GitHub stars</strong
          > and nearly <strong>24,000 weekly NPM downloads</strong>. This rapid
          adoption indicates a strong community interest and support, essential
          factors for the sustainability of any open-source project.
          Additionally, the backing from Vercel further solidifies its
          credibility in the market.
        </p>

        <h2>Key Features Driving Popularity</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Ease of Use</strong>: Developers with basic knowledge of
            HTML, CSS, and JavaScript can easily implement Shadcn UI components.
            The library's straightforward installation methods (copy-paste or
            CLI) lower the barrier to entry.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Accessibility</strong>: Adhering to Web Content
            Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG), Shadcn UI ensures that applications
            built with it are accessible to all users, including those utilizing
            screen readers and keyboard navigation.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Customization Options</strong>: Shadcn UI allows developers
            to modify component source code directly, providing fine-grained
            control over design and functionality. This level of customization
            is particularly beneficial for projects requiring specific design
            elements.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Conclusion: A Strong Contender in the Market</h2>
        <p>
          Shadcn UI represents a shift in how developers approach building user
          interfaces. Its unique model of providing reusable components combined
          with modern technology stacks positions it as a strong contender among
          existing libraries. As trends continue to evolve in web development,
          Shadcn UI's focus on flexibility and accessibility is likely to keep
          it at the forefront of the industry.
        </p>
      </article>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>
